<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HOSPITAL BOARD MEMBERS NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors has canceled Tuesday's election for 
the South Bay Hospital District Board and appointed Ken Johnson and Patricia 
Allen Dreizler to seats on the board. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, a current member of the board who was running for reelection, and 
Dreizler, who was seeking election, were appointed after the third candidate 
for the two seats withdrew from the race in August. 
</P>
<P>
Under those circumstances, supervisors can cancel an election and fill seats by 
appointment. 
</P>
<P>
The district provides money for public health programs in Manhattan Beach, 
Hermosa Beach and Redondo Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Dick Fruin, an attorney who served on the board from 1980 through 1984, 
declined Tuesday to say why he changed his mind about the campaign. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, who is community services director of the county Beaches and Harbors 
Department, and Dreizler, who retired last year as Redondo Beach community 
resources director, will be sworn in Dec. 6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
