<DOCNO> LA110190-0021 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 300911 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 1, 1990, Thursday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 8; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
262 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 18-year-old Mira Mesa night school student was shot to death during a fight 
with a classmate near Mason Elementary School in the 10000 block of Arrow Rock 
Avenue, police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Maru Angelo Sharpe of San Diego was dead on arrival shortly after 8:30 p.m. 
Tuesday at Sharp Memorial Hospital in La Jolla, the county coroner's office 
said. 
</P>
<P>
He had been shot once in the chest with a small-caliber handgun, police said. 
</P>
<P>
A 17-year-old youth was arrested in connection with the shooting and booked 
into Juvenile Hall on a murder charge, according to Lt. Dan Berglund of the 
homicide division. The teen-ager came home after the shooting, told his mother 
he had been in a fight and he thought he had shot someone, and she called 
police, Berglund said. 
</P>
<P>
Sharpe and two male students and one female student had gone to dinner after 
class at the adult school of Mira Mesa High let out about 7:30 p.m. They were 
dropping off the girl at Mason Elementary School near her home, Berglund said. 
When Sharpe continued talking to the girl, the driver of the car became 
irritated at having to wait, and words were exchanged between the two, Berglund 
said. 
</P>
<P>
A fist fight broke out, and Sharpe beat up the teen-ager, who then threatened 
to kill Sharpe and drove away, Berglund said. Sharpe, the girl and the other 
male classmate walked across the street and continued their conversation until 
the suspect returned about 15 minutes later and shot Sharpe once in the chest, 
he said. 
</P>
<P>
Sharpe lived with his father, Richard, in the 9000 block of Sawtooth Way in San 
Diego. 
</P>
</TEXT>
