<P>
Stikkitty, a hard rock band from Fullerton, has won the $20,000 first prize in 
an international contest for unsigned bands that was decided Sunday with a live 
"battle of the bands" in Tokyo. The 16 finalists, representing 15 countries, 
were alloted six minutes each to play for a panel of judges in the "Band 
Explosion" festival at the Budokan Theatre, Stikkitty's manager, Jeff Gurzi, 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
