The panel included Bon Jovi's producer, Bruce Fairbairn, as well as David Paich 
and Steve Lukather of Toto and Spike, singer for the British band London 
Quireboys. The victory brings Stikkitty's winnings for the contest to $30,000 
(the band won $10,000 and a free recording session with a major producer 
earlier this month when it was named the U.S. champion). Stikkitty will play 
Nov. 25 at the Coach House in San Juan Capistrano, opening for Sweet. 
