<P>
Rock Loses a Round: Rock fans in England received some bad news Wednesday when 
the government decided that Britain's new commercial FM station will feature 
music "other than pop or rock." This is bad news not only for fans but also for 
the various rock stars -- such as Phil Collins, Robert Plant, David Bowie, and 
Elton John -- who lobbied for a rock format on the country's just-formed 
commercial FM station. It is expected that the station, which is to be 
operational in late 1991, will feature classical music. CLAUDIA PUIG 
