<TEXT>
<P>
Feathers Ruffled Over 'Wings': Two writers who claim that their ideas were used 
as the basis for the NBC series "Wings" are suing Paramount Pictures, NBC and a 
producer. 
</P>
<P>
In the suit, filed in Los Angeles Superior Court, writers Russell Scott and 
Mark Anderson claim that they sent story lines to Paramount in 1988 for "Fly by 
Knight," a situation comedy based on an airline. The material was returned, 
they said, but not before it was allegedly opened and used as the basis for the 
show. A Paramount spokeswoman said that the studio had no comment on the suit. 
