<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reuters to Cut 300 Jobs: The international news and financial services agency 
announced that it will cut 300 jobs, 200 of them in Britain, because of 
"difficult and unsettled" market conditions. Reuters also said it will delay 
the launch of Dealing 2000, an improved system for electronically providing 
foreign exchange information to traders. The layoffs represent 6% of its 
British payroll and 3% of its worldwide work force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
