and liabilities will be taken over by Van Nuys-based Live in exchange for a 
package of Live equity securities. However, Vestron, which distributes home 
videos and holds the rights to some 1,200 films including such hits as 
"Platoon" and "Dirty Dancing," will first file for Chapter 11 bankruptcy 
protection. 
