<TEXT>
<P>
A pregnant woman from Paramount was wounded Wednesday during a robbery attempt 
in Long Beach, the third pregnant woman in a week who has fallen victim to a 
street shooting in Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
Maria Lopez, 29, was struck once in the abdomen, and her companion, Mark Robert 
Arias, 31, of Long Beach was shot and killed as they sat in a parked car at 
12:45 a.m., police said. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez was in guarded condition after surgery at a Paramount hospital, officials 
said. Her 5-month-old fetus was not struck by the bullet and was in good 
condition. 
</P>
<P>
Another pregnant woman was critically wounded as she stood on a porch in South 
Los Angeles, and a 38-year-old pregnant woman was shot to death last week as 
she walked with her boyfriend in West Los Angeles. 
