<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREGNANT WOMAN IS SHOT; 
</P>
<P>
CRIME: SHE IS THE THIRD WOUNDED BY GUNFIRE IN THE COUNTY IN A WEEK. SHE AND A 
COMPANION WERE VICTIMS OF A ROBBERY ATTEMPT. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN H. LEE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The third pregnant woman in a week has fallen victim to a street shooting in 
Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
The most recent victim, Maria Lopez, 29, of Paramount, was wounded early 
Wednesday during a robbery attempt in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez was struck once in the abdomen and her companion, Mark Robert Arias, 31, 
of Long Beach, was shot and killed as they sat in a parked car at 12:45 a.m., 
Police Detective Ron Pavek said. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman demanded money from the couple and started shooting when Arias 
replied that he only had $3, Pavek said. 
</P>
<P>
With Arias unconscious in the driver's seat, Lopez managed to drive to Charter 
Suburban Hospital in Paramount, where she underwent surgery. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez was in guarded condition Wednesday afternoon, hospital spokesman Allen 
Meadows said. The 5-month-old fetus was not struck by the bullet and was in 
good condition, Meadows said. 
</P>
<P>
On Monday evening, another pregnant woman was standing on the porch of a home 
in South Los Angeles when she was struck once in the head by a bullet. 
</P>
<P>
Kara Cooper, 20, was taken to County-USC Medical Center, where she was in 
extremely critical condition. Cooper's 8-month-old fetus was not injured, 
hospital spokeswoman Adelaida de la Cerda said. Witnesses told police 
investigators that the unidentified gunman fled into an alley. 
</P>
<P>
On Oct. 24, a 38-year-old woman was gunned down as she walked home with her 
boyfriend in a West Los Angeles neighborhood, Police Detective Elliot Rada 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The detective said Pauline Ellis, who was expecting to give birth in a month, 
died in a hail of bullets that may have been meant for her 29-year-old 
boyfriend because of a previous dispute with the gunmen. 
</P>
<P>
"The weather was nice for walking, and (Ellis) had to get out and exercise a 
little to relieve the discomfort of being eight months pregnant," Rada said. 
"She would have had a baby girl if she and the fetus had lived." 
</P>
<P>
In Orange County, a pregnant woman was shot Tuesday as she left her 
gynecologist's office. 
</P>
<P>
Janet C. Totten, 29, of Westminster was treated at Hoag Memorial Hospital in 
Newport Beach for a single rifle shot wound to the face, Lt. Ed McErlain said. 
She was listed in satisfactory condition and her 5-month-old fetus was not 
harmed, McErlain said. 
</P>
<P>
Totten told investigators that she had obtained a temporary restraining order 
against her husband, Anthony L. Totten, 32, for alleged death threats to her 
and her unborn child. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach police arrested Anthony Totten on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
