<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL OFFICER ANSWERING SILENT ALARM KILLS KIDNAP, RAPE SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A school police officer, responding to a silent alarm at a Compton elementary 
school before dawn Wednesday, shot and killed a man who allegedly kidnaped a 
woman at knifepoint and ordered her to disrobe in an apparent rape attempt, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
James Calvin Williams, 30, of Compton was struck in the head by a single shot 
fired by the officer and was pronounced dead at Washington Elementary School. 
</P>
<P>
Police withheld the identities of both the 31-year-old woman and the school 
officer, an 11-year veteran of the Compton Unified School District Police 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was not injured. She told investigators that she was making a call at 
a pay telephone about a block and a half from the school when her assailant 
threatened her with a knife and took her to the school grounds. 
</P>
<P>
Compton Police Sgt. Barry Lobel said the school district officer responded to a 
silent alarm and arrived at the school about 3:20 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
When he got out of his car to unlock a gate, Lobel said, the officer heard a 
woman yell and saw Williams, armed with an assault knife with a 6-to-8-inch 
blade, approaching the victim, who was partially clothed. 
</P>
<P>
The officer fired once, Lobel said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
