SPOTLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the first six games of the season, Tony Williams was a good player on a 
losing team; last week he was a great player on a winner. 
</P>
<P>
Williams rushed for 176 yards and scored four touchdowns, including the 
game-winner with 30 seconds remaining, to help Ventura break a 10-game losing 
streak with a 46-45 victory over Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
Williams scored on runs of 10, eight, one and one yards. All four touchdown 
runs came on a play called 44 Blast, a play that Williams ran 10 times for 74 
yards in the game. 
</P>
<P>
"He was the go-to guy," Ventura Coach Dick James said. "He ran harder and with 
more enthusiasm than he has all year." 
</P>
<P>
Tony Williams: Ventura 
</P>
<P>
Football: Running back 
</P>
