<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE WINS CROSS-COUNTRY TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Glendale College, powered by the one-two finish of Hugo Allan Garcia and Obed 
Aguirre, clinched the Western State Conference men's cross-country title with a 
victory at Moorpark College on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Garcia, who has won seven of his eight races this season, smashed his previous 
course record by 1 minute 6 seconds with a time of 19:48 over the four-mile 
route. 
</P>
<P>
Aguirre placed second in 20:14 as the Vaqueros totaled 32 points. 
</P>
<P>
Bakersfield placed second with 38 points, followed by Ventura with 77. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale's other scorers were Fred Mirzaian (sixth in 21:14), Oscar Perez (11th 
in 21:51) and Rick Provenzano (12th in 21:54). 
</P>
<P>
The WSC title was the second in three years for the Vaqueros, who qualified for 
the Southern California regional meet at Irvine Regional Park in Tustin on Nov. 
9. 
</P>
<P>
Nicole Jimenez finished seventh to lead the Glendale women to a second-place 
finish with 76 points. Moorpark won with 21 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
