<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gustav Weder and Curdin Morell of Switzerland won the two-man bobsled 
competition in the first World Cup event of the season at Calgary, Canada's 
Olympic Park. 
</P>
<P>
Their combined time for two runs was 1:55.24. 
</P>
<P>
In his international bobsled debut over a regulation 1,500-meter course, Edwin 
Moses of Newport Beach, a two-time Summer Olympic gold medalist in the 
intermediate hurdles, teamed with veteran driver Brian Shimer of Naples, Fla., 
to finish eighth in 1:56.33. They were first among three U.S. teams. The 
four-man competition is scheduled for Saturday. 
</P>
