<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
RAIDERS; 
</P>
<P>
ROSTER SHOULD KEEP THEM GUESSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Raiders have some important roster decisions to make before Sunday's key 
divisional game against Kansas City, but they seem willing to keep the Chiefs 
guessing until the last minute. 
</P>
<P>
Eligible to return from injured reserve are cornerback Garry Lewis (collarbone 
injury), tight end Mike Dyal (hamstring injury) and tackle Bruce Wilkerson 
(knee injury). 
</P>
<P>
Will they or won't they play? 
</P>
<P>
Only Raider Coach Art Shell knows for sure. 
</P>
<P>
Lewis, the starting left cornerback, seems the surest bet to face the Chiefs. 
"There's a good chance he'll be on the roster," Shell said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Wilkerson? "He's looking pretty good; he's feeling much better," Shell offered. 
"There's a chance he may be on the roster." 
</P>
<P>
Dyal? "We're not sure right now." 
</P>
<P>
The Raiders are also fairly sure that defensive end Mike Wise will return this 
week from an ankle sprain. CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</TEXT>
