<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
RAMS; 
</P>
<P>
ROBINSON: NO FINGER-POINTING AT 2-5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The team met Wednesday to regroup in the wake of its dip to 2-5 after Monday 
night's dismal 41-10 loss to the Steelers in Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
"We talked fairly extensively about it," Coach John Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't see any withdrawal or recriminations, no finger-pointing. We talked 
about it. We have to be concerned that there isn't just a numbness about 
everything. It's almost as though you build a little cocoon around yourself to 
kind of ward off the pain. We've got to stand up and do something about it and 
not just absorb it." 
</P>
<P>
Cornerback Jerry Gray said that since coming back from arthroscopic knee 
surgery a month ago, his play has been hampered by a nagging insecurity about 
the injury. Tuesday, he had an X-ray that showed no further serious damage, but 
Gray said the knee still isn't close to being 100%: "Out there Monday, I felt 
like I had no burst." TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
