<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Marcida Dodson and Jackson Sellers 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEN. VASQUEZ?: Supervisor Gaddi H. Vasquez is showing up on political pundits' 
short list of possible successors to Sen. Pete Wilson if Wilson is elected 
governor. . . . Vasquez is one of the Republican Party's young stars, and 
appointing him to the Senate could boost Wilson's standing among Latino voters. 
</P>
<P>
Though flattered to be mentioned, Vasquez says only: "For the time being, the 
most important thing is to get Pete Wilson elected." 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
The Party Line 
</P>
<P>
Republican candidates for governor have carried Orange County since 1970, 
except in 1978, when Brown edged Younger. Percentage of votes per party: 
</P>
