<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Marcida Dodson and Jackson Sellers 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PROOF WANTED: Scientists have yet to prove there are other solar systems. . . . 
Now comes UC Irvine physics professor Rognvald Garden. With a $25,000 grant 
from the Rockwell International Trust, the Shetland Islands native is building 
an astronomical camera and spectrometer that he hopes will witness the birth of 
planets around distant stars. "Ours will be the only infrared instrument around 
able to detect motions of gases" that are forming planets, he said. Marcida 
Dodson and Jackson Sellers 
</P>
