<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; 
</P>
<P>
KREBER APPOINTED TO MUNICIPAL COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian on Wednesday appointed Municipal Court Judge Ronald P. 
Kreber as a Municipal Court judge in Laguna Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
Kreber, 53, replaces Judge David C. Velasquez, who was elevated to Orange 
County Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
Kreber, of Laguna Beach, has been a Municipal Court judge in Fullerton since 
1988. He maintained a private law practice in Newport Beach for nine years 
before his appointment to the bench, and served as a deputy district attorney 
in Orange County for seven years before that. 
</P>
<P>
Kreber was also a Los Angeles police officer from 1963 to 1972. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Ronald P. Kreber Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
