<P>
DREAM DOCTOR WINS SIRES QUALIFICATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Dream Doctor earned his fourth win in five lifetime starts when he posted 
the fastest qualifying time for the estimated $75,000 California Sires Cup 
Derby on Wednesday night at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
The 10 fastest horses from Wednesday's trials will return for the final Nov. 
10. 
</P>
<P>
The Dream Doctor won the first of two trials for the 400-yard stake for 
3-year-old California-breds. The gelded son of Merridoc covered the 400 yards 
in 20.01 seconds while defeating Here Comes the Band, which had the second 
fastest qualifying time of 20.10 seconds. 
</P>
