<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rock 'n' roll pioneer Chuck Berry is suing the magazine High Society, saying it 
published stolen nude photos of him with several women. 
</P>
<P>
In the suit filed Monday in St. Louis Circuit Court, Berry claims that the 
magazine published eight photographs of him posing with unidentified nude women 
as the cover story for its January edition. 
</P>
<P>
The suit says the photos were stolen and claims their publication violated 
Berry's privacy. 
</P>
<P>
Calls to the magazine's office Wednesday were not returned. 
